resources.string:
This app is for learning the aural (sound) components of music theory.
It aims to support people with visual impairments by utilising voice control and text-to-speech.
There are pitch matching exercises, in which you hear a pitch and match that pitch with your voice;
interval exercises, in which you do the same thing only with two notes in succession;
scale exercises, in which you do the same thing with a musical scale;
and melody exercises, in which you do the same thing with a unique melody.
If there is any bits of terminology you don\'t understand, you can view the terminology menu to see a list of terms and their meanings.
If you need any help with the voice commands, say \'help\'.
